longBusinessSummary: Mongolian Mining Corporation is involved in the mining, processing, transportation, and sale of coking coal products in China. It owns and operates the Ukhaa Khudag and the Baruun Naran open-pit coking coal mines located in South Gobi province of Mongolia. It is also involved in the railway project management, airport operation and management, water exploration and supply management, and power supply project management activities; and trading of coal and machinery equipment. The company was incorporated in 2010 and is headquartered in Ulaanbaatar, Mongolia.
